Opening elevation: -4.09 m or 906.798 m at Sub datum A, -4.06 m or 906.780 m at Sub datum B.
Soil Locus 29 throughout and soil Locus 12 in the southeast.
Closing elevation: -4.80 m or 906.088 m at Sub datum A, -4.98 m or 905.860 m at Sub datum B.

This Dark Reddish Brown soil (Munsell 2.5YR 4/3) included several column drums and a plethora of large ashlars. Unlike Locus 5, the destruction layer is densely packed with artifactual remains and with collapsed debris both from the south terraces and the temple proper. The small column base could be associated with a colonnaded walkway above the terraces since it is unlike any architectural feature in the site. The artifactual remains indicate little about the use of this area and appear to be a conglomeration of different period’s material.

Phase XI: Further collapse post-CE 5th c., possibly the result of the earthquake of 512. Fill accumulates following the disuse of the canalization systems. The remains of two bodies are found in the upper level fluvial deposits. Localized burning in some areas.
